    "instructions": [
        "Bring 4 cups of water to a boil in a medium pot with 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook pasta for 8 minutes. Reserve 1/2 cup pasta water, drain, and toss with 1/2 tsp oil.",
        "Heat 2 tbsp oil in a large pan over medium heat. Sauté onion with a pinch of salt until translucent (2 mins). Add garlic, cook for 30s.",
        "Add all bell peppers and cook until slightly tender (2 mins). Stir in pasta, scallions, and habanero (if using). Cook 1 minute.",
        "Reduce heat to medium-low. Stir in allspice and thyme; cook 2 mins until fragrant.",
        "Add half-and-half and bring to a slow simmer. Stir in mozzarella until a creamy sauce forms (2 mins). Season with salt to taste."
